대뇌, 소뇌, 뇌간, 뇌실, 뇌실질 외 공간에 출혈, 종괴, 수두증, 위축, 과거의 허혈성 병변 등의 주요 이상 소견 없음.

Circle of Willis의 주요 뇌동맥과 경동맥에 협착, 폐쇄, 동맥류 소견 없음.
Conclusion: Normal brain MRI.

Findings:
CI, CLL, CT abnormality (Lt frontal lobe).
Axial T1WI, sagittal T1WI, axial T2WI, axial FLAIR, axial T2* GRE image, axial DWI, intracranial TOF MRA 획득하였으며 neck MRA에 대해서 조영증강을 시행함.

<Brain, CSF space, and related findings>
Multifocal areas of restricted diffusion at the left frontal-parietal-temporal, and right frontal-parietal lobes, and right caudate nucleus (head).
 -> Acute infarctions 
Hyperintense cortical vessels on FLAIR adjacent to the infarcted brain.
 -> Most likely due to slow leptomeningeal collateral flows.
Encephalomalacia at the Rt frontal lobe.

<MRA>
Focal severe stenoses at the Lt cavernous and supraclinoid ICA, Lt proximal A1 segment, Rt A2, and Lt distal V4 (dominant VA).
Focal moderate stenosis at the Rt proximal M1 segment.
Diffuse mild to moderate stenosis of the Rt petrocavernous ICA.

Focal severe stenoseis at the Lt VA origin.
Complete occlusion of the Rt VA origin with distal flow reconstution at the distal V2 segment.
Focal moderate stenosis at the Lt subclavian artery, distal to the VA origin.

<Skull, PNS, orbits, and temporal>
Unremarkable.
Conclusion:
1. Acute infarction at the Lt cortical border-zone, and Rt ACA territory.
2. Multifocal stenoses of the intracranial, and cervical arteries.
3. Encephalomalacia at the Rt frontal lobe.
